title: For Sale:  Gun Transfers
postcontent:
A1armorer performs firearms transfers for the low price of $15.00. 

You can purchase the firearm from any dealer in the USA and have it shipped to our shop in Hayden, AL. This makes interstate and internet sales convenient for our customers. 

Wherever you buy the gun they are going to need a copy of our FFL in order to ship the gun to us. Upon request we can mail or e-mail them a copy of our license. The Seller will then send the gun to us for you to pick up.

To pick up the gun, you will need a valid Alabama Driver's License or government photo identification and you'll need to fill out a Federal Form 4473 for the background check. Once all of these are complete, and your background check is approved, you can pay your transfer fee and take your gun home.

We do our best to make the process as simple as possible.

http://www.a1armorer.com

This gives you a smooth recoil system with a much longer sight radius but with the same length 16" barrel as a carbine.  This is chambered in 5.56 and has a 1:9" twist.  This rifle has an A2 buttstock installed, Magpul handguards with 4 Magpul rail sections installed on it.  Command Arms forward stubby grip is included as well.  It also has a DPMS 3 Prong flash hider installed on it.  It handles very nicely and functions 100%.  Although not pictured, (9) 30rd magazines are included with it.  

This is not a cheapy "sporter" type model that have dropped the price on alot of AR15's recently.  I know you can go to Walmart and buy a DPMS Sporter model for $600, this isn't the same model and isn't in the same league quality wise.  It's a full mil-spec gun, all metal parts gun.  It's a very unique rifle that you don't see very often...I just have several AR's at the moment and got in a bit of financial bind and need to free up some cash.
